question.title: ProGuard obfuscating classes even after `keep class` flag. Affecting Android WebView behavior

node.contents: I'm using ProGuard to obfuscate my Android app.

astNode.text: I'm using ProGuard to obfuscate my Android app.

node.contents: I'm also using WebView to show a webpage (an HTML walkthrough page) that contains a button that will close the WebView. There is a function in the Javascript that calls back a closeWalkthrough() method:

astNode.text: I'm also using WebView to show a webpage (an HTML walkthrough page) that contains a button that will close the WebView. There is a function in the Javascript that calls back a closeWalkthrough() method:

node.contents: The releated Java class looks like this:

astNode.text: The releated Java class looks like this:

elements.contents: package com.myclass.android; import android.app.Activity; import android.content.Context; import android.webkit.JavascriptInterface; public class JavaScriptInterface { Context _context; JavaScriptInterface(Context context) { _context = context; } @JavascriptInterface public void closeWalkthrough() { ((Activity) _context).finish(); } }

units.rawText: package com.myclass.android; import android.app.Activity; import android.content.Context; import android.webkit.JavascriptInterface; public class JavaScriptInterface { Context _context; JavaScriptInterface(Context context) { _context = context; } @JavascriptInterface public void closeWalkthrough() { ((Activity) _context).finish(); } }

node.contents: I've added the following flags in my ProGuard file in hopes that it won't obfuscate the JavaScriptInterface class because, if I understand it correctly, the Javascript method MyClass.closeWalkthrough() is looking for the closeWalkthrough() found in my JavaScriptInterface Java class.
